  <result type="1">
   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output 1.1:
Maritime Law Enforcement agencies in Ghana and Nigeria respectively have the knowledge, capacity and capability to conduct arrests at sea and prepare cases for prosecution</narrative>
   </title>
   <reference code="269953" vocabulary="99"></reference>
   <indicator aggregation-status="0" ascending="1" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Number of arrests leading to prepared cases for prosecution</narrative>
    </title>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
     <target value="Teams operational and conducting sea operations with results"></target>
     <actual value="In Ghana, UNODC has recruited 3 national MLE mentors embedded in Navy, and fisheries department in Tema and Takoradi. First ever interagency maritime operation including involvement of Attorney General&apos;s officer in August 2020. Tracked and investigating 14 vessels and arresting 4 for being involved in Illegal, Unreported and Unregulated Fishing.

In Nigeria a MLE mentor has been supporting the Navy until the pandemic closed the country in March 2020. Due to the pandemic no further activities have been possible in 2020."></actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2019-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2019-12-31"></period-end>
     <target value="Specialized maritime crime teams established in Ghana and Nigeria"></target>
     <actual value="In Nigeria, the Harmonised Standing Operating Procedures (HSOP) Secretariat is currently managed by the Ministry of Justice. UNODC has provided its technical assistance to include an Addendum on evidence collection. Further, UNODC has assisted the national government in the efforts to establish an inter-agency maritime crime team to operationalise the HSOP Addendum on evidence collection.

In Ghana, two Task Forces in Tema and Takoradi are established. The Navy, Marine Police, a Fisheries Enforcement Unit and Ministry of Justice officers, comprises them."></actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-12-31"></period-end>
     <target value="At least ten arrests and five cases initiated for prosecution"></target>
     <actual value="Nigeria has arrested and prosecuted 10 pirates in 2021 (100 % output). Ghana hasn&apos;t approved their anti-piracy law yet, why the output is 0%"></actual>
    </period>
   </indicator>
  </result>
